    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nIf the last line in a file gets pushed off screen by a `virtual_lines` diagnostics it doesn't get redrawn when the `virtual_lines` disappears (for instance due to `current_line=true`) until there is a syntax highlighting event or a change of mode. In the following video I consistently trigger this bug:\n\nhttps://github.com/user-attachments/assets/2ada7494-e51b-4375-9e47-7ba040617b68\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\nI have no idea how to include diagnostics without packages, sorry. If you want I can try to create a minimal config using `vim.pack` and `nvim-lspconfig` plus an LSP (the video includes `texlab`, I guess it also should be reproducible with `lua_lsp`).\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nThe line being displayed as it should be.\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\n0.12.1\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nI don't think VIM supports virtual_lines diagnostics\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nArch Linux\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nsakura 3.8.9\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-256color\n\n### Installation\n\nArch repo",
